DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(-6,6,1);
$b = random(-6,6,1);
$c = random(-6,6,1);
$d = random(-6,6,1);
$e = random(-6,6,1);
$f = random(-6,6,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
The expression \( \displaystyle \left(\frac{x^{$a} y^{$b} z^{$c} }{(xy)^{$d} z^{$e}} \right)^{$f}\) equals
\(x^ry^sz^t\) $BR where \(r\), the exponent of \(x\), is:
\{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = ($a-$d)*$f;
ANS(num_cmp($ans, mode=>"strict"));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and \(s\), the exponent of \(y\), is:
\{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = ($b-$d)*$f;
ANS(num_cmp($ans, mode=>"strict"));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and finally \(t\), the exponent of \(z\), is:
\{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
[NOTE:  Your answers cannot be algebraic expressions.]
$BR
EOT

$ans = ($c-$e)*$f;
ANS(num_cmp($ans, mode=>"strict"));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.

